Title : Gregorio Álvarez (historian)
Text : [[File:Don gregorio.jpg|thumb|Gregorio Álvarez.]]

'''Gregorio Álvarez''' (Ranquilón, [[Ñorquín Department|Ñorquín]], [[Territory of Neuquén]], 28 November 1889 – 11 October 1986) was an Argentine historian, physician and writer.

==Biography==
Álvarez became a teacher in 1910. In 1919 he graduated as a medical doctor at the [[University of Buenos Aires]], specializing in [[dermatology]]. He was a founder of the Argentine Dermatological Association.

In 1950 he explored the [[Copahue]] hotsprings.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.rionegro.com.ar/diario/2008/05/05/20085v05s09.php |title = The work of Gregorio Álvarez |publisher = Río Negro |date= 5 May 2008}}</ref> He also made research on [[infantile eczema]], obtaining the golden medal from Jammes Laboratories, Paris, in 1954.<ref>[http://www.labandurria.com.ar/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=563:el-v-congreso-de-historia-regional-del-neuquen-homenajeara-a-gregorio-alvarez&catid=56:educacion&Itemid=55 El V Congreso de Historia Regional del Neuquén homenajeará a Gregorio Álvarez ]</ref>

Álvarez explored Neuquén Province on horseback, studying its culture.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laangosturadigital.com.ar/v2/noticia.php?id_noticia=7405&origen=web|title=AVC Noticias cumple 5 años al aire|last=yayo|website=www.laangosturadigital.com.ar|language=es-ES|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref>

The dinosaur genus [[Alvarezsaurus]] and the family [[Alvarezsauridae]] are named in his honor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laso.com.ar/web_dinos/texto4.htm|title=Untitled Document|website=www.laso.com.ar|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref> He died on 11 October 1986 at the age of 96.

